history.text: Hello, what movie will we talking about?
the notebook with ryan gosling
Oh I've heard of that but never saw it.  What do you know about it?  I may want to see it
it is a romantic story set in the 1940s,between young lovers
Who else is in the movie?
rachel mcadams as the romantic interest  and joan allen and james marsden
Do you know how long the movie is?
i am not sure about that but i can say that the movie is engaging
Thats okay, is it a Romantic Drama or Comedy?
it is a romantic drama , adapted based on a novel of the same title
Do you know when the movie came out?
in 2004 by director nick cassavetes
What studio made it?
not sure but you may check online,it has a 52% rotten tomatoes score
Do you know if it won any awards?
i did not know any but the movie is well acted and it has a good material, some touching scenes
Does it have a sad ending?  I hate sad endings.
i did not want to spoil anything , but sure you will not  be disapointed, it was delightful
so you would recommend it then?
yes definitely i would reccomend
Nice, are there any other movies that it is similar to?
i cant think of any ,so far this is the one for me
is the acting good?
Gosling and  specially Mcadams give all star performance, left the audience with touching scenes
Do you know of any other Mcadams has been in?
Sorry do you know any other movies Mcadams has been in?
sorry i am not familiar with any film mcadams has been in so far.by the way the notebook is in the top of the summer movies on the time it was release
it sounds like it is a really good movie.
Do  you know where I can watch it?
well the it is about an 17 year old  heiress, after seeing her on a carnival, they have a summer love affair.
you can rent or buy the dvd. well thank you have a nice day

uid1response.feedback: Most of my questions were answered well about the movie so I would probably see it based on the answers given.  My last question wasn't answered and the last answer the other person gave didn't have anything to do with my question.  I asked where I could see the movie and they told me what it was about instead with no mention of my question.  I wonder if it was a real person I was talking to.
